HEADWORD: Piculet
<hw>Pic"u*let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<er>Picus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of very small
woodpeckers of the genus <gen>Picumnus</gen> and allied genera. Their
tail feathers are not stiff and sharp at the tips, as in ordinary
woodpeckers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picus</ent>⟦br⟧
